// bug.md #8 follow-up: statically resolving calls in every expression position.
// Making `uses` file-scoped (bug #8) removed a global-scope name leak that had
// been masking two checker gaps — a call under `!` and a call inside a lambda
// body were never type-checked, so they were not statically resolved and only
// worked while the leak dumped namespace names into the global scope. Both are
// now type-checked. Here a namespaced function is reached through each position.
namespace Lib {
    bool isFive(string s) => s == "5";
    int inc(int x) => x + 1;
    void run() {
        if (!isFive("4")) console.writeln("not five");   // call under `!`
        var f = () => inc(20);                            // call in a lambda body
        console.writeln(f());
    }
}
uses Lib;
Lib::run();
